  <description type="morphology">Plants with fibrous strands of leaves at base, 9--42.5 cm. Leaves erect from sheath, shorter than scapes, 6--24.5 cm; sheath 3.5--5 cm &amp;#61620; 1.5--5 mm, ligule not hoodlike, unlobed; blade 0.8--2.9 mm wide, apex acute. Inflorescences: scape often purple near base, mostly exceeding leaves, 5.5--27.2 cm &amp;#61620; 1--2.1 mm; racemes 5.1--21.4 cm &amp;#61620; 2--5 mm; pedicel 0.4--4.5 &amp;#61620; 0.1--0.5 mm. Flowers: tepals elliptic, 1.1--1.6 &amp;#61620; 0.7--0.9 mm, apex round; pistils 6, 3 fertile, 3 sterile. Fruits: fruiting receptacles with wings; schizocarps linear, 7--8.3 &amp;#61620; 0.8--1.2 mm; mericarps linear, weakly ridged abaxially, 6.5--8.5 &amp;#61620; 0.5--1.5 mm, beak erect, 0.3 mm. 2n = 24.</description>
